    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/can-sap-s-odata-framework-be-used-as-api-endpoint/qaq-p/13674384</id>
    <title>Can SAP's OData Framework be used as API endpoint?</title>
    <updated>2024-04-18T11:36:51.656000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>a_sirotin</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/876072</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hello together,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;can the OData Interfaces be seen as alternative of RFC? Because it seems OData is only an interface for browser-based apps like UI5, but it cannot be used for API endpoints.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;According to following reference, OData is not really REST-full since its not stateless due to the usage of cookies. Also the X-CSRF-Token is actually only designed for browser:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;A href="https://security.stackexchange.com/questions/166724/should-i-use-csrf-protection-on-rest-api-endpoints" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://security.stackexchange.com/questions/166724/should-i-use-csrf-protection-on-rest-api-endpoints&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;How do you see SAP's OData? Is there maybe differences between RAP-OData and the ODatas you create via Tx SEGW? Background is, I hear concerns in my company regarding security standards and that such interfaces actually cannot be used as API endpoints.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thank you.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/can-sap-s-odata-framework-be-used-as-api-endpoint/qaq-p/13674384"/>
    <published>2024-04-18T11:36:51.656000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
