    <content>&lt;P&gt;In &lt;STRONG&gt;SAP Business ByDesign&lt;/STRONG&gt; (byD), the &lt;STRONG&gt;OData Editor&lt;/STRONG&gt; allows the creation of &lt;STRONG&gt;Custom OData Services&lt;/STRONG&gt;.&amp;nbsp;We are trying to create a new &lt;STRONG&gt;Engineering Change Order&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;of type &lt;STRONG&gt;Single-date Order&lt;/STRONG&gt; using a custom OData service but it is always failing.&amp;nbsp;We have isolated the problem in a smaller custom OData service but the problem is still the same. We are able to create a &lt;STRONG&gt;Standard Order&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;(so the service works) but if the creation of a &lt;STRONG&gt;Single-date Order&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;is attempted, it is failing because the &lt;STRONG&gt;StartDate&lt;/STRONG&gt; is required. Trying to add the &lt;STRONG&gt;StartDate&lt;/STRONG&gt; into the custom OData service does not work: trying to call the service does not create the new ECO. Is there a way to create a &lt;STRONG&gt;Single-date Order&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;ECO using a custom OData service?&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/cannot-create-a-single-date-order-eco-using-a-custom-odata-service/qaq-p/13682671"/>
    <published>2024-04-25T17:34:25.428000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
